You can pass a function.
Like:

filter: getFilter

function getFilter(value, index, list) {
    return value[ $sope.dynamicThing] == $scope,filterValue;
}

You can also construct your filter object dynamically

filter: myDynamicObject

And construct it as you wish, on form submit or on watch or whatever.

Complete dom: http://plnkr.co/edit/KBUduWoX4BueJwZlaSln?p=preview
